Health Minister Ummy Mwalimu has warned over an outbreak of yellow fever in the country following the eruption of the same in neighboring Kenya. Using twitter handle @wizara_afyatz, the Ministry of Health tweeted that the Minister Ummy issued the waning after received a report from the World Health Organization (WHO) on March 3, this year, stating that there was an outbreak of the disease in Kenya. So far there are no reports of the disease in the country, according to the Health Ministryâ€™s monitoring system. According to her, as of March 3, this year, Kenya reported 15 cases and three deaths. She, however, alerted all referral hospitals in the country to get ready for yellow fever testing services for travelers and those in need and instructed border health officials to ensure that travelers entering from infected countries have vaccination certificates.